HEADWORD: Catapetalous
<hw>Cat`a*pet"al*ous</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Pref.
<ets>cata</ets> + <ets>petalous</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Bot.)</fld>
<def>Having the petals held together by stamens, which grow to their
bases, as in the mallow.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Cataphonic</ent>⟦br⟧
